SIMPLE: aslant
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aslant
<hw>A*slant"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>adv. & a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>a-</ets> + <ets>slant</ets>.]</ety> <def>Toward one side; in a
slanting direction; obliquely.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[The shaft] drove through his neck <qex>aslant</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aslant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Aslant
<hw>A*slant"</hw>, <pos>prep.</pos> <def>In a slanting direction over;
athwart.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There is a willow grows <qex>aslant</qex> a brook.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Asleep</ent>⟦br⟧
